description._content: Description: A perch for frigate birds on the terrace of "Ao-n te Tarine". These birds are much prized by the natives for sporting purposes. Location: Kiribati ------------------------------------------------------ Description: A tame frigate bird on his perch: the tame birds are used as decoys for capturing wild ones. Location: Kiribati ------------------------------------------------------ Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/642. This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons. Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown.
